race.comment: JAKIVY (1) has been good in two runs back from a spell and looks ready to go third up. The fresh run here in a BM62 was good before tackling a handy race at Flemington and finding the line strongly for fourth. Comes back a couple of grades now and looks well placed. OLIVIA ROSE (10) is hard to knock. She keeps racing well, getting the deserved maiden win at Sandown Lakeside two back with a dominant win, good again at Seymour when just run down late. She'll roll forward and take catching again. LITTLE BIGHORN (7) has placed in both runs back from a spell, beaten at short odds last time but working home well without the best of luck. He can improve. LAPLAND (6) resumed with a tidy maiden win at Mornington and is open to plenty of upside. GOLDEN AGE (9) was rewarded for consistency with a solid win at Terang last time and has each-way claims.
